Step 2: Since U8 = UScalar .U8 has the field bv : BitVec 8 and val = bv.toNat, equal val implies equal bv (by BitVec.eq_of_toNat_eq or similar), hence equal U8 values.

Step 3: Two arrays (Array U8 32#usize) are equal if their underlying lists are equal. Use Subtype.ext to reduce to showing a.val = b.val (as lists). Use List.ext_getElem! or similar, together with the fact that both lists have length 32.

Use U8x32_byte_recovery, Subtype.ext, List.ext, and the fact that UScalar values are determined by their .val field.
